description.en: The ontology represents AI risk concepts and relations based on the AI Act draft and ISO 31000 standard series.

comment.en: Represents controls with the purpose of eliminating an event from happening.
An AI customer is an organization or entity that uses an AI product or service either directly or by its  provision to AI users. [Source: ISO 22989]

label.en: An AI service provider is an organization or entity that provides AI services  either  directly usable by an AI customer or user, or to be integrated into a system using AI along with non-AI components. [Source: ISO 22989]

Other organizations or entities impacted by an AI system, service or product can be for example in the  form of an individual or a community. For example, consumers who interacts with a social network that provides recommendations based on AI, drivers of vehicles with AI-based automation. [Source: ISO 22989]
Ability to meet stakeholder expectations in a verifiable way. [Source: ISO 22989]

comment.en: Represents purpose of monitoring and evaluating performance and behavior of employees in workplace.
The entity that receives data and a problem specification and creates an AI model. [Source: ISO 22989]
Represents the measure that maintains and/or modifies risk. [Source: ISO 31000, 3.8]
Refers to a group of persons such as citizens, marginsalised groups, etc.
the ability of an AI system to achieve its intended purpose [Source: AI Act, Article 3(18)]
Represents a type of AI system that addresses a broad range of tasks with a satisfactory level of  performance
Refers to education and vocational training

predicting the occurrence or reoccurrence of an actual or potential criminal offence based on profiling of natural persons or assessing personality traits and characteristics or past criminal behaviour of natural persons or groups
Ability of a system to recover operational condition quickly following an incident. [Source: ISO 22989]

An AI auditor is an organization or entity that is concerned with the audit of organizations producing, providing or using AI systems, to assess conformance to standards, policies or legal requirements. [ISO 22989]
inputs designed to cause the model to make a mistake
Represents controls that do not involve human intervention.

A data subject is an organization or entity that is affected by AI systems with following aspects: 
— Subject of training data: where data pertaining to an organization or human is used in training an  AI system, there can be implications for security and privacy, for the latter particularly where that subject is an individual human. [Source: ISO 22989]
Regulators are organizations and entities that have the authorities to set, implement and enforce the legal requirements as intended in policies set forth by policy makers. [Source: ISO 22989]
An AI producer is an organization or entity that designs, develops, tests and deploys products or services that use one or more AI system. [Source: ISO 22989]
Property of an AI system that allows a human or another external agent to intervene in the system’s functioning. [Source: ISO 22989]
A data provider is an organization or entity that is concerned providing data used by AI products or services.
Represents a right, freedom, or principle set out in the EU Charter of Fundamental Rights.

An AI partner is an organization or entity that provides services in the context of AI. AI partners can  perform technical development of AI products or services, conduct testing and validation of AI products and services, audit AI usage, evaluate AI products or services and perform other tasks. Examples of AI partner types are discussed in the following subclauses. [Source: ISO 22989]
Refers to migration, asylum and border control management
Refers to manipulating or generating image content.
Represents the main approaches and techniques used for development of AI systems.

Represents the extent to which potentially harmed or adversely impacted persons are in a vulnerable position due to an imbalance of power, knowledge, economic or social circumstances, or age. [Source: AI Act]
type of AI system that is focused on defined tasks to address a specific problem. [Source: ISO 22989]
Refers to degree to which data has attributes that correctly represent the true value of the intended attribute of a concept or event in a specific context of use. [ISO 22989, 3.4.3]
Specifies the extent to which the outcome produced with an AI system is easily reversible.

An AI provider is an organization or entity that provides products or services that uses one or more AI systems. AI providers encompass AI platform providers and AI product or service providers. [Source: ISO 22989]

Policy makers are organizations and entities that have the authorities to set policies within an international, regional, national or industrial domain that can have an impact on an AI system, service or product. [Source: ISO 22989]
Represents the sector/domain the AI system is intended to be used in.

use of an AI system in a way that is not in accordance with its intended purpose, but which may result from reasonably foreseeable human behaviour or interaction with other systems [Source: AI Act, Article 3(13)]
Represents any individual, group or organization that can affect, be affected by or perceive itself to be affected by a decision or activity [Source: ISO/IEC TR 24028, 3.37]
the entity that verifies that the AI model is performing as designed. [Source ISO 22989]
The use of an AI system in a way that is not in accordance with its intended purpose.
Outcome of an event affecting objectives. [Source: ISO 31000, 3.6]
Represents areas that AI might have impact on.
Attack trying to manipulate the training dataset
Refers to the purpose of assessing students in educational and vocational training institutions and for assessing participants in tests commonly required for admission to educational institutions.
Represents primary output of an AI system when provided with input data or information. [Source: ISO 22989]
Represents tendency of automatically relying or over-relying on the output produced by an AI system
Ability of a system to maintain its level of performance under any circumstances. [Source: ISO 22989]
Represents a functional element that constructs an AI system. [Source: ISO 22989]
Refers to employment, workers management and access to self-employment
Represents purpose of researching and interpreting facts and the law.

any incident that directly or indirectly leads, might have led or might lead to : (a) the death of a person or serious damage to a person’s health, to property or the environment, (b) a serious and irreversible disruption of the management and operation of critical infrastructure [Source: AI Act, Articl3 3(44)]
Refers to manipulating or generating video content.

label.en: An AI system integrator is an organization or entity that is concerned with the integration of AI components into larger systems, potentially also including non-AI components. [Source: ISO 22989]

comment.en: the entity that receives an AI model and specifies what computation to  execute (the implementation to use and on what compute resources, for example CPU, GPU, ASIC, FPGA). [Source ISO 22989]
Intervention of  a system's operation
Refers to incompentece of individuals to whom human oversight is assigned.
Authorities are organizations or entities that can have an impact on an AI system, service or product.

label.en: Lack Of Appropriate Instruction For Use

comment.en: Refers to the purpose of determining access or assigning natural persons to educational and vocational training institutions.
Refers to profiling of natural persons in the course of detection, investigation or prosecution of criminal offences.
An AI subject is an organization or entity that is impacted by an AI system, service or product.
Refers to manipulating or generating audio content.
An AI evaluator is an organization or entity that evaluates the performance of one or more AI systems. [Source: ISO 22989]

label.en: Disruption Of Operation Of Critical Infrastructure

comment.en: Indicates an element that has the potential give rise to a risk.
Represents controls that are implemented using a technology.
Property of a system that appropriate information about the system is made available to  relevant stakeholders. [Source: ISO 22989]
Chance of an event happening. [Source: ISO 31000, 3.7]

Refers to use of AI systems for making individual risk assessments of natural persons in order to assess the risk of a natural person for offending or reoffending or the risk for potential victims of criminal offences.
Interruption of a system's operation
Property of an AI system to express important factors influencing the AI system results in a  way that humans can understand. [Source ISO 22989]
An AI user is an organization or entity that uses AI products or services. [Source: ISO 22989]
An AI platform provider is an organization or entity that provides services that enable other stakeholders to produce AI services or products. [Source: ISO 22989]

deploying subliminal techniques beyond a person’s consciousness in order to materially distort a person’s behaviour in a manner that causes or is likely to cause that person or another person physical or psychological harm

Refers to the use for which an AI system is intended by the provider, including the specific context and conditions of use, as specified in the information supplied by the provider in the instructions for use, promotional or sales materials and statements, as well as in the technical documentation. [Source: AI Act, Art 3(12)]
An AI developer is an organization or entity that is concerned with the development of AI services and products. [Source: ISO 22989]
the extent to which an AI system has been used or is likely to be used
Represents consequences related to bias.
The entity that verifies that a computation is being executed as designed. [Source: ISO 22989]
degree to which a product or system provides the correct results with the needed degree of precision. [ISO 22989, 3.4.4]
Property of an AI system that enables reliable assumptions by stakeholders  about the output. [Source: ISO 22989]
Examination of applications for asylum, visa and residence permits and associated complaints
Represents occurrence or change of a particular set of circumstances. [Source ISO 31000, 3.5]
the purpose of identifying natural persons at a distance through the comparison of a person’s biometric data with the biometric data contained in a reference database
Filtering applications for recruitment or selection of natural persons.
Property of consistent intended behaviour and results. [Source: ISO 22989]
Represents controls performed by humans without any use of technologies.
Weakness of a system can be exploited by one or more threats. [Source: ISO/IEC TR 24028, 3.48 with modifications]
inacurracy of the predictions, recommondations, or decisions produced by the system.
Represnets controls that comprise a combination of automated and manual controls.

Represents a software that is developed with one or more of the AI Approaches and can, for a given set of human-defined objectives, generate outputs such as content, predictions, recommendations, or decisions influencing the environments they interact with. [Source: AI Act, Art 3(1)]
Indicates a risk (of harm) associated with an AI system.

An AI product provider is an organization or entity that provides AI products either directly usable by an AI customer or user, or to be integrated into a system using AI along with non-AI components. [Source: ISO 22989]
Systematic difference in treatment of certain objects, people, or groups in comparison to others [ISO 22989]
Indicates stakeholders of an AI system
Indicates the AI techniques used in an AI system.

label.en: Indicates the intended purpose of an AI system.

comment.en: Indicates the industry (context) the AI system is intended to be used in.
Indicates vulnerabilities of an AI system.
Indicates that a component is part of an AI system.
